result.shortName: WEST JAPAN RAILWAY CO UNSPON AD

assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: West Japan Railway Company provides passenger railway transport services in Japan. The company operates through Transportation Operations, Retail Business, Real Estate Business, and Other Businesses segments. As of March 31, 2022, it operated a route length of 4,903.1 kilometers, comprising Shinkansen route of 812.6 kilometers and conventional lines of 4,090.5 kilometers; and 1,174 stations. The company also engages in the provision of bus and ferry services; selling of goods and food services; operation of department stores, convenience stores, restaurants, souvenir shops, shopping centers, and others, as well as hotels; selling and leasing of real estate; credit cards and electronic money; and travel and construction business. The company was incorporated in 1987 and is based in Osaka, Japan.
